I hate it when you slip back
into ratchet-speak. You know why?

15:59.416 --> 16:02.670
Because I don't want my Virgil
talking like that.

16:02.753 --> 16:05.005
I don't want him to struggle like you did.

16:05.089 --> 16:09.259
Hey! Don't get it twisted. I was born
in the struggle. So was our son.

16:09.343 --> 16:13.055
Just because you don't like to hear it out
of my mouth doesn't mean it's not true.

16:13.138 --> 16:14.974
You don't look for solutions,
just problems.

16:15.057 --> 16:16.725
We need to find a solution.

16:17.768 --> 16:19.478
Virgil's trying to be something he's not,

16:19.561 --> 16:21.981
he's acting all hood,
trying to get his Brownsville on,

16:22.064 --> 16:24.233
-imitating you.
-The boy doesn't know who he is

16:24.316 --> 16:26.318
because you're raising him
like race doesn't matter.

16:26.402 --> 16:28.570
He might be light-skinned like you,
but the boy's black.

16:28.654 --> 16:31.782
Are you telling me
I don't know how to raise my black son?

16:33.200 --> 16:35.119
Virgil can see you're halfway
out the door.

16:35.202 --> 16:37.955
You pushed me out! You got me
sleeping in the fucking basement!

16:38.038 --> 16:39.790
Because you're fucking other women!

16:39.873 --> 16:41.792
[baby crying nearby]

16:48.382 --> 16:53.012
-We fell out. We can't hide it.
-How do you think our son is taking it?

16:54.555 --> 16:57.057
By putting on a modern age minstrel show.

16:59.935 --> 17:04.898
I've been doing everything I can
to figure out how to be separated

17:05.482 --> 17:07.443
and still live under the same roof.

17:09.486 --> 17:12.531
But it's taking its toll on Virgil.

17:15.242 --> 17:17.911
We at least have to be
a united front for him.

17:17.995 --> 17:21.040
Cheryl, I'm here, aren't I? I'm here.

17:21.123 --> 17:24.793
This video is Virgil crying out
for our attention.

17:24.877 --> 17:27.212
Yeah, well, you best believe
I'mma talk to him.

17:31.175 --> 17:34.094
[sniffing]

17:35.179 --> 17:36.180
What is that?

17:36.764 --> 17:39.475
One of your new colognes? I don't like it.

17:39.558 --> 17:40.893
It's called Ocean Wave.

17:41.769 --> 17:45.230
What the hell is that supposed to mean?
Are you trying to be cryptic?

17:45.314 --> 17:47.024
If I was, would you even care?

17:48.525 --> 17:49.526
We're gonna be late.

17:52.821 --> 17:57.034
Did any other parents complain about
the outrageousness of this music video?

17:57.826 --> 17:59.787
The other parents never called me.

18:00.496 --> 18:03.957
You and your husband are the only ones
to take issue with this.

18:04.041 --> 18:07.461
I almost think that you don't understand
the gravity of the situation, Mr. Howard.

18:08.212 --> 18:12.257
My wife and I aren't paying
this elite school $45,000 a year

18:12.341 --> 18:15.094
to see our son degrade himself
using the word "nigger"

18:15.177 --> 18:17.596
and to see other white
and non-black students use

18:17.679 --> 18:19.973
an incendiary and dangerous epithet
so freely.

18:20.057 --> 18:22.267
-It was an assignment.
-An assignment?

18:22.351 --> 18:25.604
Virgil and his classmates
were given a class assignment

18:25.687 --> 18:28.857
to create something that would go viral...

18:29.608 --> 18:31.693
and their music video did just that.

18:32.361 --> 18:33.195
Their...

18:34.404 --> 18:40.410
"'N-word' For Love" music video
has racked up over 500,000 YouTube views.

18:40.494 --> 18:43.622
I wonder if the other parents
would have felt it was an issue

18:43.705 --> 18:46.583
if this song was entitled
"Kikes For Love."

18:46.667 --> 18:51.088
Or "Chinks for Love" or "Micks For Love,"
"Spics For Love," "Pollocks For Love,"

18:51.171 --> 18:53.215
"Spaghetti Benders For Love,"

18:53.298 --> 18:54.883
"Red Skins For Love,"

18:54.967 --> 18:57.344
or even "Faggots For Love."

18:57.427 --> 19:01.598
Would they pivot on their opinion
on just how vile this song is?

19:01.682 --> 19:03.392
[Cheryl] Mr. Howard, I was just thinking.

19:03.475 --> 19:08.063
I have a former classmate of mine
from Yale Law School, class of 2002,

19:08.147 --> 19:11.525
and she is white, by the way,

19:11.608 --> 19:14.611
who is an esteemed columnist
for <i>The New York Times.</i>

19:15.612 --> 19:22.494
I wonder how she would frame this story
about Heights Prep's subtle endorsement

19:22.578 --> 19:28.292
of white and non-African American
students' liberal use of the--

19:28.876 --> 19:32.462
Not even going to use
the politically correct term, "N-word."

19:32.546 --> 19:34.256
Let's just call it what it is.

19:34.339 --> 19:38.552
...the word "nigger" for a school project.

19:38.635 --> 19:41.889
Mr. and Mrs. Overstreet, you...

19:42.806 --> 19:45.517
are absolutely 100 percent right.

19:47.019 --> 19:49.688
I fell asleep at the wheel
in my duties here,

19:49.771 --> 19:56.737
and I can only offer my own apology
and an apology on behalf of Heights Prep.

19:58.197 --> 20:02.951
[clears throat] I will have
the "Nigger For Love" music video

20:03.035 --> 20:04.786
deleted immediately from YouTube,

20:04.870 --> 20:10.542
and this kind of insensitivity
will never happen again on my watch.

20:11.460 --> 20:12.586
You have my word.

20:14.588 --> 20:16.089
Oh, by the way, um...

20:16.673 --> 20:22.179
My late father marched side by side
with Dr. King in Selma, Alabama.

20:24.306 --> 20:27.017
#BlackLivesMatter.

20:35.943 --> 20:37.653
-Thank you very much.
-Thank you.

20:42.282 --> 20:43.617
[exhales]

20:45.160 --> 20:47.496
[door opens, closes]

20:56.755 --> 20:59.174
-What are you doing here, Ms. Darling?
-What do you mean?

20:59.258 --> 21:03.470
You told me you wanted
to meet with me at 3:30. It's 3:30, right?

21:04.054 --> 21:07.432
Oh! As a matter of fact,
I am ten minutes early.

21:07.516 --> 21:11.853
You are 24 hours and ten minutes early,
Ms. Darling.

21:11.937 --> 21:14.523
Our meeting is not
until tomorrow afternoon at 3:30.

21:15.107 --> 21:17.526
-Can I have a seat, please?
-Please be my guest.

21:17.609 --> 21:21.405
-Thanks. [sighs]
-[chuckles]

21:21.822 --> 21:26.076
I know how it is when somebody
got you sprung, trust me.

21:26.702 --> 21:29.079
But that ain't none of my BI.

21:29.162 --> 21:32.249
All due respect, Ms. Moss, you're right,
that is none of your business.

21:32.332 --> 21:38.005
I agree. But you know what is my BI?
These students and their personal welfare.

21:38.088 --> 21:41.508
That's Raqueletta Moss' BI.
I care about them.

21:41.591 --> 21:43.552
Are you saying I don't care?

21:44.011 --> 21:46.722
Because I do. I care about these students
more than you know.

21:46.805 --> 21:50.726
Oh, Ms. Darling, on the contrary.
Raqueletta Moss knows that you care.

21:51.393 --> 21:54.771
Raqueletta Moss admires your work
and your love for the children.

21:55.439 --> 21:57.733
But you don't know the level of trauma...

21:58.317 --> 22:02.904
the level of sexual trauma
some of these students have experienced.

22:02.988 --> 22:03.822
But I...

22:06.533 --> 22:07.367
Excuse me.

22:09.536 --> 22:11.830
Raqueletta Moss knows that kind of trauma.

22:12.456 --> 22:16.209
And Raqueletta Moss believes, despite
your noble intentions, Ms. Darling,

22:16.293 --> 22:19.796
that using art
to confront personal dysfunction

22:19.880 --> 22:22.215
is a self-fulfilling defect.

22:22.299 --> 22:24.426
A broken record that never stops skippin'.

22:25.761 --> 22:28.221
You mind if Raqueletta Moss
shares something personal with you?

22:28.305 --> 22:29.431
Okay.

22:29.514 --> 22:31.892
Raqueletta Moss comes
from that same environment

22:31.975 --> 22:33.393
that Reggie was born into.

22:34.227 --> 22:39.357
Raqueletta Moss was one of those
chicken-heads cluckin' in the back rooms,

22:39.441 --> 22:44.696
fuckin' grown-ass crack monster men
when she was just 13 years old.

22:45.322 --> 22:48.700
Raqueletta Moss is the product
of a cracked-out single mom,

22:48.784 --> 22:53.663
who pimped her overdeveloped daughter
in dark project hallways.

22:54.206 --> 22:57.250
Raqueletta Moss was shuffled
like a deck of marked cards

22:57.334 --> 22:58.710
in the foster care system.

22:59.544 --> 23:04.549
Raqueletta Moss thanks God every day
that she was adopted from a group home

23:04.633 --> 23:07.177
by Albert and Tina Lewis,
who lived in Canarsie,

23:07.260 --> 23:09.930
and put Raqueletta Moss
on the straight and narrow.

23:10.680 --> 23:14.351
After graduating
with her master's in education from LIU

23:14.434 --> 23:17.687
on the corner of Dekalb and Flatbush,
across the street from Junior's,

23:17.771 --> 23:22.734
Raqueletta Moss vowed to help kids succeed
with love, compassion, and discipline.

23:23.360 --> 23:25.278
Raqueletta Moss would like
to help Ms. Darling

23:25.362 --> 23:27.155
deepen her empathy
for students like Reggie

23:27.239 --> 23:30.408
and realize that emotional scars
are like still waters,

23:30.492 --> 23:32.869
but they run deeper than deep.

23:33.662 --> 23:36.164
Do you understand
what Raqueletta Moss is--

23:38.583 --> 23:39.417
Sorry.

23:40.961 --> 23:43.630
Do you understand what I'm trying
to say to you, Ms. Darling?

23:44.464 --> 23:46.925
I... think I do.

23:47.008 --> 23:50.971
Quick question, do you often refer
to yourself in the third person?

23:54.057 --> 23:56.977
We all have our ways of coping,
Ms. Darling.

23:58.645 --> 23:59.980
Have a good afternoon.

24:00.063 --> 24:03.233
<i>♪ Save yourself, save yourself ♪</i>

24:04.067 --> 24:08.196
<i>♪ Save yourself, save yourself ♪</i>

24:08.280 --> 24:09.906
[whimpering]

24:09.990 --> 24:13.577
<i>♪ Hear your pain and misery ♪</i>

24:13.660 --> 24:17.455
<i>♪ Trying to love me ♪</i>

24:17.539 --> 24:21.168
<i>♪ Hear your pain and misery ♪</i>

24:21.251 --> 24:25.881
<i>♪ Trying to love me ♪</i>

24:25.964 --> 24:28.925
<i>♪ Save yourself ♪</i>

24:29.009 --> 24:32.137
Did you and Mom really have
to come to the school, Dad?

24:32.220 --> 24:33.972
Son, the world's on fire right now.

24:34.556 --> 24:37.517
And that word you were using
so carelessly, that word "nigger,"

24:37.601 --> 24:39.436
it's the gasoline igniting the flames.

24:39.519 --> 24:41.229
There's nothing cool
about using that word,

24:41.313 --> 24:43.481
especially a young black man
using it so freely

24:43.565 --> 24:45.817
around young white kids
who have no historical reference.

24:45.901 --> 24:49.237
Everyone calls each other "nigga"
at Heights Prep, whatever race you are.

24:49.321 --> 24:50.322
It's not a big thing.

24:50.405 --> 24:53.742
But you don't. I taught you that word
isn't something to play with.

24:53.825 --> 24:55.994
We say it because we're cool
with each other.

24:56.077 --> 24:58.538
-[scoffs]
-It's all love between us.

24:58.622 --> 25:00.624
My generation is different.

25:00.707 --> 25:04.586
Different like that white boy,
Dylann Storm Roof, in Charleston,

25:04.669 --> 25:07.505
who walked into Emanuel AME Church
and murdered nine innocent people?

25:07.589 --> 25:10.967
Different like him? 'Cause he used
that word too. You're too smart for this.

25:12.052 --> 25:15.555
You're so talented with your music.
Whose idea was this video?

25:15.639 --> 25:18.642
It was just a cool thing to do.
I got mad views.

25:18.725 --> 25:20.644
I was recognizably black for a change.

25:20.727 --> 25:24.564
You are black, Virgil. You don't have
to act no kind of way to prove it.

25:24.648 --> 25:26.316
I know, but my friends don't.

25:27.192 --> 25:29.528
Are your friends
all that's important to you right now?

25:29.611 --> 25:30.904
There's something more important.

25:30.987 --> 25:34.491
These white and Asian kids,
are they down for you as you are for them?

25:34.574 --> 25:36.701
What do you care?
You're getting divorced and leaving.

25:36.785 --> 25:38.495
-Right?
-Wait, hold up. Slow your roll.

25:39.079 --> 25:40.830
Mind how you talkin' to me.

25:44.125 --> 25:49.381
I will never abandon you, Virgil. Never.
You understand me? Do you understand me?

25:49.464 --> 25:52.634
-I understand.
-What's happening between me and your mom

25:52.717 --> 25:54.678
has nothing to do with you, know that.

25:54.761 --> 25:58.139
You walk around the house like a ghost.
We don't even play <i>Madden</i> anymore.

25:58.223 --> 26:00.725
That's because you kept
whooping my butt at <i>NBA 2K</i>.

26:00.809 --> 26:04.521
-You told me I had to be ten times better.
-Than your white friends, yeah.

26:04.604 --> 26:09.359
But you gotta take it easy
on your old man. I've got arthritis.

26:09.442 --> 26:11.695
[both chuckling]

26:11.778 --> 26:13.530
-Dad?
-Yeah?

26:13.613 --> 26:16.533
I don't fit in at Heights Prep.
I do, but I don't.

26:16.616 --> 26:19.327
You and Mom should've just sent me
to public school instead.

26:19.411 --> 26:22.664
When I was at private school,
I felt like I didn't belonged either.

26:22.747 --> 26:26.459
It was the same thing, going home
every day from school to the projects.

26:27.127 --> 26:30.630
So, I understand
your double consciousness,

26:30.714 --> 26:32.048
living between both worlds.

26:33.049 --> 26:35.302
But that's what it's like being black
in America today.

26:35.385 --> 26:38.054
Today? Dad, it's always been like that.

26:38.138 --> 26:43.435
That's why you don't do what they do.
You find folks who do what you do.

26:44.477 --> 26:45.770
-A'ight?
-All right.

26:46.938 --> 26:49.733
You remember, I love you, sun.

26:51.484 --> 26:54.779
S-U-N, 'cause you shine like one.

26:54.863 --> 26:58.366
-That's extra cheesy... but thanks.
-[chuckles]

26:58.908 --> 26:59.951
I love you too.

27:00.035 --> 27:02.078
-Cheesy, huh?
-Yeah.

27:02.162 --> 27:04.622
-Let's go for a walk by the promenade.
-All right.

27:12.756 --> 27:15.383
[ship horn blowing]

27:21.848 --> 27:23.350
[soft music playing]

27:23.433 --> 27:24.309
Wow!

27:25.685 --> 27:28.480
<i>♪ Oh, it's such a crazy world ♪</i>

27:28.563 --> 27:32.901
-Wow! Look at this one!
-I love this, these brush strokes.

27:32.984 --> 27:37.072
Oh, those are so nice.
I like the dots of paint over here.

27:38.114 --> 27:39.949
This one's so cool!

27:40.909 --> 27:41.993
I love this one.

27:42.786 --> 27:45.705
-Oh, man, this is even better.
-[chuckles]

27:45.789 --> 27:48.333
This work, it's so dope. I love it!

27:48.416 --> 27:49.876
You have real talent, Reggie.

27:50.960 --> 27:51.961
I mean it.

27:52.045 --> 27:54.923
You have this ability
to take your inner voice

27:55.006 --> 27:58.343
and blast it on speaker phone
through your images and your art.

28:00.929 --> 28:05.975
You know, the terminology
of the words "bitch," "slut," "ho,"

28:06.059 --> 28:09.938
as cool as it may seem that you can
re-purpose them to empower you,

28:10.021 --> 28:12.899
it doesn't actually increase
your currency in the world.

28:12.982 --> 28:16.403
-In fact, if you're not careful--
-I already know what you're gonna say.

28:16.486 --> 28:19.989
It can cheapen my own personal value.
That's if I let it.

28:20.073 --> 28:21.533
Don't you know that I know

28:21.616 --> 28:25.620
that girls like Nicki Minaj and Amber Rose
are playing a role?

28:25.703 --> 28:27.080
I'm not stupid.

28:27.163 --> 28:30.917
Men call them sluts, hos,
every dirty thing you can name.

28:31.459 --> 28:37.424
Yet Nicki and Amber have near 75 million
followers on Instagram combined.

28:37.507 --> 28:39.968
Being a ho can be a great business.

28:40.927 --> 28:43.972
-Do you understand what you're saying?
-Yeah, I understand what I'm saying.

28:44.055 --> 28:46.224
This is America.
That's what works for them.

28:46.307 --> 28:49.728
That's not what works for me, though.
Thank you, Ms. Darling, for the books.

28:49.811 --> 28:52.021
-See you in class next week.
-Okay.

29:00.989 --> 29:05.994
<i>♪ As you grow</i>
<i>The troubles seem to change... ♪</i>

29:06.077 --> 29:08.580
<i>Hola, </i>Nola. How you's at?

29:08.663 --> 29:10.999
You know, stayin' black, stayin' alive.

29:11.082 --> 29:12.667
Hey, honey, why don't you go to bed?

29:13.126 --> 29:14.878
-All right, Mommy.
-Okay?

29:15.670 --> 29:16.671
Okay.

29:16.880 --> 29:19.048
Gonna be right over there to tuck you in.

29:19.132 --> 29:20.884
Don't take long, Mommy.

29:20.967 --> 29:23.845
I won't. I'm just gonna finish talkin'
to Godmommy Nola.

29:23.928 --> 29:25.263
Hurry up, Mommy.

29:27.140 --> 29:31.102
[gasps] Oh, my goodness!
That's your butt now?

29:31.186 --> 29:33.980
Evidently.
She's been screaming to get out.

29:34.063 --> 29:35.899
I don't even know what to say.

29:35.982 --> 29:37.275
Say "congratulations."

29:37.358 --> 29:39.194
Congratulations.

29:39.277 --> 29:41.613
-[sighs]
<i>-Uh, what does Nadia think?</i>

29:43.156 --> 29:46.034
She thinks that it's pretty, like Nicki.

29:50.580 --> 29:55.084
<i>♪ Don't you go away ♪</i>

29:55.168 --> 29:58.129
Thank you, Mr. Overstreet. [kisses]

30:01.132 --> 30:02.467
Wow!

30:04.844 --> 30:05.678
Oh!

30:05.762 --> 30:06.971
-[knocking]
-[Ella] Nola!

30:07.055 --> 30:10.433
-I slid your mail under the door!
-Thank you, Ms. Ella!

30:22.821 --> 30:25.532
Con Ed got no love for starving artists.

30:25.615 --> 30:28.201
They will cut your shit off.

30:28.785 --> 30:29.619
Fuck.

30:31.663 --> 30:32.497
[phone dings]

30:36.292 --> 30:37.919
[Moss] <i>Dear Ms. Nola Darling...</i>

30:38.878 --> 30:42.966
Sister, I wanna give you a chance,
as I feel you have a real purpose.

30:43.466 --> 30:45.927
Let's work together
to serve these students.

30:46.553 --> 30:48.555
As my personal role model,

30:48.638 --> 30:51.391
the first African-American woman
elected to Congress

30:51.474 --> 30:53.226
and the first African-American woman

30:53.309 --> 30:55.937
to run for president
of the United States of America,

30:56.020 --> 30:59.190
<i>the late great Shirley Chisholm</i>
<i>from BK, once said,</i>

30:59.274 --> 31:03.653
"Service is the rent you pay
for room on this Earth."

31:03.736 --> 31:06.197
Raqueletta Moss speaks in the third person

31:06.865 --> 31:09.784
because she survived
her own personal Holocaust

31:09.868 --> 31:12.829
by stepping out of her body and saying,

31:12.912 --> 31:16.374
"I am not here. I am not here.

31:17.208 --> 31:20.670
You cannot hurt me,
because Raqueletta Moss...

31:21.713 --> 31:22.755
is not here."

31:22.839 --> 31:27.260
To quote one of Brooklyn's finest,
the late Notorious B.I.G.,

31:27.343 --> 31:30.054
"And if you don't know, now you know."

31:32.223 --> 31:33.850
Don't let me down, my sister.

31:34.767 --> 31:37.937
Sincerely, Ms. Raqueletta Moss.

31:46.112 --> 31:48.364
[soft piano music plays]
